1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the analysis of cascading failures in power networks, which can be considered as a type of social and information network. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper uses a percolation-based approach to study cascading failures in power networks, which can be related to the study of complex systems in neural and evolutionary computing. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a mapping between links in a random geometric graph and nodes in a corresponding dual covering graph, which can be considered as a data structure. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the problem of cascading failures in power networks, which is a topic of interest in systems and control. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses probability theory to model the failure of links in power networks, which can be related to the study of information theory.
